==English==

===Noun===

'''paleoichnology'''

# A branch of [[ichnology]] concerned with the study of [[trace fossil]]s preserved in ancient [[rock]]s.

===Quotations===
*'''1984''' The evolutionary aspect of ecology which has started to develop due to studies of trace fossils will stay long the privilege of '''paleoichnology''' - ''Palaeontology: Proceedings of the 27th International Geological Congress -- Invited Papers, Volume 2'' - International Geological Congress
*'''2003''' '''Paleoichnology''' is their historic equivalent - the study of ichnological evidence of animals of the past - ''Starring T. Rex: Dinosaur Mythology and Popular Culture'' - Jose Louis Sanz

